JOHANNESBURG – The Department of Sport and Recreation on Friday confirmed the withdrawal of the formation of a Committee of Inquiry into a stampede at the FNB Stadium in July 2017. The committee was to investigate facts and events which led to the death of two fans. At least 21 others attending the Soweto Derby match between Orlando Pirates and Kaizer Chiefs were injured in the incident, which took place on 29 July. Sports Minister Tokozile Xasa gazetted the announcement on Friday. Government Gazette notice to withdraw establishment of inquiry into FNB stadium stampede by Pieter van der Merwe on Scribd At the time, Johannesburg mayor Herman Mashaba extended his condolences to the families of the two people who died. READ: Two die and child injured in Soweto derby stampede eNCA